President Donald J. Trump spoke with Amir Sheikh Tameem bin Hamad Al Thani of Qatar and emphasized the need for all countries in the region to work together to prevent the financing of terrorist organizations and the promotion of extremist ideology. The President also stressed the importance of a united Gulf Cooperation Council and a strong United States-Gulf Cooperation Council partnership in defeating terrorism and promoting regional stability. Additionally, President Trump offered to assist in resolving the differences between the parties, including by hosting a meeting at the White House if needed.